# Task Constraints (Opus 4.6)

## Principle

Apply domain-specific constraints based on what the task involves.

---

## Constraint Matrix

| If task involves | Apply |
|------------------|-------|
| Agent core logic | Read `agent_rules/core-constitution.md` first |
| Agent runtime config | Read `agent_rules/runtime/autonomy.md` |
| Agent DB code | Read `agent_rules/database.md` + existing patterns |
| Crypto code | Read `agent_rules/crypto.md` + `crypto-ops` skill |
| RPi system ops | Read `agent_rules/shell.md` + `agent_rules/hardware.md` |
| Self-improvement | Read `agent_rules/self-improvement.md` |
| Prompt engineering | `prompt-generation` skill |

---

## Decision Criteria

- **Unsure about agent behavior?** → Check `agent_rules/`, don't guess
- **Unsure about cost?** → Calculate before calling API
- **Multiple approaches?** → Pick cheapest in tokens, note alternatives
- **New domain?** → Search for existing pattern first
